text: Genuinely impressive how many things this man was actually able to do, just insanely productive in writing, science, engineering, sports, he did it all. True early-mid 20th century type of man.

You know I'm not a huge shabbos goy for communuist China but my buddy's dad got a part for a machine for his steel cutting facility from Alibaba for 100 euro with 200 euro shipping to Bulgaria while the same thing costs 15 000 dollars from the Americans even without the shipping.

Alibaba specifically seems to have a ton of industrial machinery and very specific tools for workshops, factories, etc. for incredibly low prices. If you're in certain fields where you build physical stuff it just makes sense to do business with them from what I can see here.
Apparently they are slightly lower quality than the Western version but they still get the job done to the point where quality is not really a concern
